00:58:25,248 --> 00:58:26,425
I thought I told Dave
to take you...

986
00:58:26,496 --> 00:58:28,318
The sheriff said,
"I'm taking you

987
00:58:28,384 --> 00:58:30,522
" to the outskirts of town,
Dave Tolliver.

988
00:58:30,592 --> 00:58:32,153
" I'm leaving the rest
to your own judgment. "

989
00:58:32,224 --> 00:58:33,336
Now see here, I'm not
going to allow you...

990
00:58:33,408 --> 00:58:34,488
I ain't listening.

991
00:58:34,560 --> 00:58:37,145
You told me to get an education,
I'm getting an education.

992
00:58:37,216 --> 00:58:40,064
I'm staying here. If I can't stay
here, I'll stay where I can stay.

993
00:58:40,128 --> 00:58:42,015
You can't stop me,
nobody's gonna stop me!

994
00:58:42,080 --> 00:58:44,731
I'll show the whole kit and boodle
of you how much I can get learned.

995
00:58:44,800 --> 00:58:46,425
I'll be smarter than you!
That's what I'll be!

996
00:58:46,496 --> 00:58:48,252
Now listen, you little
stick of dynamite.

997
00:58:48,320 --> 00:58:49,564
You're getting
out of here now.

998
00:58:49,632 --> 00:58:50,941
You're going back
up in the mountains.

999
00:58:51,008 --> 00:58:52,503
I've heard enough of you
and I've seen enough of you.

1000
00:58:52,576 --> 00:58:54,965
For the present, at least.
Now, come on, get out.

1001
00:58:56,576 --> 00:58:57,688
You...

1002
00:58:59,616 --> 00:59:01,209
All right, I'll go

1003
00:59:02,912 --> 00:59:04,603
if you want me to go.

1004
00:59:04,928 --> 00:59:06,008
Sure.

1005
00:59:06,976 --> 00:59:09,432
I don't want people
not to want me.

1006
00:59:10,784 --> 00:59:12,158
Wait a minute.

1007
00:59:12,736 --> 00:59:14,395
How did you do that?

1008
00:59:14,656 --> 00:59:15,998
Oh, that.

1009
00:59:19,168 --> 00:59:22,299
You did it
when you pushed me down.

1010
00:59:23,040 --> 00:59:24,415
I'm sorry.

1011
00:59:25,248 --> 00:59:26,393
It might have been
a rusty naiI or something.

1012
00:59:26,464 --> 00:59:28,319
We'd better fix it up.
Come over here.

1013
00:59:34,720 --> 00:59:36,858
So that's it, is it?

1014
00:59:36,928 --> 00:59:39,383
And I thought you were just
interested in the coaI business.

1015
00:59:39,456 --> 00:59:40,504
She's hurt her hand.

1016
00:59:40,576 --> 00:59:43,740
You've killed your future,
around here, anyway.

1017
00:59:43,808 --> 00:59:46,077
You're not satisfied with
one enemy, you make two.

1018
00:59:46,144 --> 00:59:47,518
You realize
what you've done?

1019
00:59:47,584 --> 00:59:50,454
Now the Falins hate you, the
Tollivers will never forgive you.

1020
00:59:50,528 --> 00:59:52,284
The Tollivers, why?
That's why.

1021
00:59:52,351 --> 00:59:55,286
That girI's gonna go back
to the mountains, now.

1022
00:59:55,360 --> 00:59:57,749
She didn't come here to start
any trouble, it just happened.

1023
00:59:57,824 --> 01:00:00,475
She's got a mind of her own, and
if she wants to stay here she can.

1024
01:00:00,544 --> 01:00:01,820
In this town?
Impossible.

1025
01:00:01,888 --> 01:00:03,132
I'll take her
to Brighton.

1026
01:00:03,200 --> 01:00:04,956
Or Plenny or Sand Creek. It
doesn't matter where you take her

1027
01:00:05,024 --> 01:00:06,333
around here, you're
about to meet Tollivers.

1028
01:00:06,400 --> 01:00:08,123
All right, I'll take her
to Louisville to my sister.

1029
01:00:08,192 --> 01:00:09,785
What do you think of that?
Nothing.

1030
01:00:09,856 --> 01:00:11,383
Except that
I'm flabbergasted.

1031
01:00:11,456 --> 01:00:12,765
Nonplussed.

1032
01:00:12,832 --> 01:00:13,977
And if you
don't mind me saying so,

1033
01:00:14,048 --> 01:00:16,153
I think you're just
a little bit nuts.

1034
01:00:18,048 --> 01:00:19,324
Thank you.

1035
01:00:21,024 --> 01:00:22,300
Both of you.

1036
01:00:55,616 --> 01:00:58,649
Mr. Hale! Oh, Mr. Hale!
You forgot the hat.

1037
01:00:58,720 --> 01:00:59,832
Thanks, Leo.

1038
01:01:09,376 --> 01:01:10,488
Well, here you are.

1039
01:01:10,560 --> 01:01:11,640
Do I...

1040
01:01:11,712 --> 01:01:13,949
Are you sure your
sister will recognize me?

1041
01:01:14,016 --> 01:01:15,674
I don't see
how she can miss.

1042
01:01:15,744 --> 01:01:17,151
Do I look all right?

1043
01:01:17,216 --> 01:01:19,638
My dear young lady,
reticent as I am by nature,

1044
01:01:19,711 --> 01:01:21,140
it behooves me at
this moment to tell you

1045
01:01:21,216 --> 01:01:23,005
that you're wearing the
finest the city affords.

1046
01:01:23,072 --> 01:01:24,348
All aboard!

1047
01:01:25,216 --> 01:01:27,126
Well, you better get on.

1048
01:01:31,456 --> 01:01:34,652
Ain't... Ain't you
gonna kiss me goodbye?

1049
01:02:03,104 --> 01:02:04,730
Well, that's over with.
Is it?

1050
01:02:04,800 --> 01:02:07,004
Yeah. What do
you mean, " Is it"?

1051
01:02:07,072 --> 01:02:08,446
No, I mean, I'm glad it's over with.

1052
01:02:08,512 --> 01:02:09,854
Are you?

1053
01:02:09,920 --> 01:02:11,447
She's nuts.
Is she?

1054
01:02:11,520 --> 01:02:13,014
Sure she is.
Any fooI can see that.

1055
01:02:13,088 --> 01:02:15,030
Well, perhaps, that's
why I'm a little stupid.

1056
01:02:15,104 --> 01:02:16,348
Yeah, maybe that's...

1057
01:02:16,416 --> 01:02:17,942
Say, what is this
"isn't " and " is she"?

1058
01:02:18,016 --> 01:02:19,194
My dear fellow,
if you'll allow me,

1059
01:02:19,264 --> 01:02:21,533
let us take " isn't "
and " is she. "

1060
01:02:21,600 --> 01:02:24,317
" Is" is that we both know,
I hope, is a verb.

1061
01:02:24,383 --> 01:02:26,969
" It" is a neuter gender,
and she is the feminine.

1062
01:02:27,040 --> 01:02:30,269
Thus, we have the neuter and
the feminine, but no masculine.

1063
01:02:30,336 --> 01:02:33,019
" What? No masculine,"
you say, then I say...

1064
01:02:33,088 --> 01:02:34,364
" I'm nuts,"
that's what you say.

1065
01:02:34,432 --> 01:02:35,959
Yeah, that's right,
you're nuts!

1066
01:02:36,032 --> 01:02:37,723
She's in love
with you, Jack.

1067
01:02:37,792 --> 01:02:39,614
In love? Who?
June.

1068
01:02:39,680 --> 01:02:40,792
Are you crazy?

1069
01:02:40,863 --> 01:02:41,846
No, no, that's already
been settled.

1070
01:02:41,919 --> 01:02:43,032
You're the one
who's crazy.

1071
01:02:43,104 --> 01:02:46,104
Why, she's been goo-gooing,
gee-geeing all over you

1072
01:02:46,176 --> 01:02:47,485
ever since
we started the camp.

1073
01:02:47,552 --> 01:02:49,243
Don't talk nonsense.

1074
01:02:49,312 --> 01:02:52,061
In love. Why, she only came
down to camp to bring Buddie.

1075
01:02:52,127 --> 01:02:53,622
In love with me.
You're an idiot.

1076
01:02:53,695 --> 01:02:55,037
I hope so.

1077
01:02:55,359 --> 01:02:57,050
I sincerely hope so.

1078
01:03:04,064 --> 01:03:05,820
The camp, Thurber.
It's on fire!

1079
01:04:02,207 --> 01:04:03,963
A bunch of fellows came over
the hill carrying torches.

1080
01:04:04,031 --> 01:04:05,242
The fellow leading
him was a-shooting.

1081
01:04:05,312 --> 01:04:06,457
The Falins.

1082
01:04:06,528 --> 01:04:08,350
Well... Never mind, we'll
talk about that later.

1083
01:04:08,416 --> 01:04:09,725
I'll get the stock
out of the corral.

1084
01:04:09,791 --> 01:04:12,344
You get the instruments
and maps out of there.

1085
01:05:10,719 --> 01:05:13,021
So that's how
you want it, is it?

1086
01:05:13,888 --> 01:05:16,987
All right, you skulking
coyotes, I'll play your game.

1087
01:05:17,056 --> 01:05:19,095
They're not gonna let me...

1088
01:05:19,967 --> 01:05:23,644
I'll put this road through if I have to
use your dirty rotten bodies for ties.

1089
01:05:24,640 --> 01:05:28,022
I'll do it if I have to hire every
man in Gaptown to finish the job.

1090
01:05:53,983 --> 01:05:55,161
If you could have seen it

1091
01:05:55,231 --> 01:05:57,141
I know you would have split your sides a
- laughing.

1092
01:05:57,215 --> 01:06:00,827
I was sitting there mending, and I
hear the dripping and the sizzling,

1093
01:06:00,895 --> 01:06:03,284
and I says to myself,
I says, " I bet a rooster

1094
01:06:03,360 --> 01:06:05,215
" it's the soft soap
a- boiling over. "

1095
01:06:05,280 --> 01:06:06,262
And sure enough...

1096
01:06:06,336 --> 01:06:08,921
Better try some of these
dandelion greens, son.

1097
01:06:08,991 --> 01:06:11,708
Zeke Denker fetched
them over this morning.

1098
01:06:11,776 --> 01:06:12,758
I ain't hungry.

1099
01:06:12,831 --> 01:06:14,293
But, David, you gotta eat something

1100
01:06:14,368 --> 01:06:16,156
after all the plowing
you've done.

1101
01:06:16,607 --> 01:06:17,720
Pappy.

1102
01:06:18,464 --> 01:06:21,595
A is the first letter
in the alphabet.

1103
01:06:21,727 --> 01:06:25,688
Because it means
"And" " Apple" and " Ax. "

1104
01:06:30,080 --> 01:06:31,868
What's this one, Pappy?

1105
01:06:31,936 --> 01:06:33,528
You mean this one?

1106
01:06:35,840 --> 01:06:38,807
Offhand I'd say
it's alike an ox yoke.

1107
01:06:38,880 --> 01:06:40,822
Didn't Mr. Hale tell you?

1108
01:06:41,248 --> 01:06:43,004
He told me
but I forgot.

1109
01:06:43,072 --> 01:06:45,690
It ain't like
no Tolliver to forget.

1110
01:06:45,759 --> 01:06:47,963
Now, if I would
have been told...

1111
01:06:49,536 --> 01:06:51,324
You know what that is?

1112
01:06:53,055 --> 01:06:54,004
Yeah.

1113
01:06:54,655 --> 01:06:56,216
Civilization!

1114
01:07:01,183 --> 01:07:02,427
David, you oughtn't
to have done that!

1115
01:07:02,495 --> 01:07:03,706
I'm through pretending.

1116
01:07:03,776 --> 01:07:05,401
Like you've been doing
all of last month.

1117
01:07:05,471 --> 01:07:06,551
Saying things
you didn't mean.

1118
01:07:06,623 --> 01:07:07,670
I'm getting sick
of the whole thing.

1119
01:07:07,743 --> 01:07:10,645
Now, son, look, you
gotta keep your shirt on.

1120
01:07:10,719 --> 01:07:14,199
If it's June you're worrying
about, she'll be back pretty short.

1121
01:07:14,271 --> 01:07:15,286
No, she ain't.

1122
01:07:15,360 --> 01:07:17,499
She ain't never coming back.
Not the June I know.

1123
01:07:17,568 --> 01:07:19,390
Ain't nothing gonna
be the way it was.

1124
01:07:19,456 --> 01:07:21,944
Look at Buddie,
even he's different.

1125
01:07:22,239 --> 01:07:23,897
So are you.
Me?

1126
01:07:23,967 --> 01:07:25,178
Yes, you are.

1127
01:07:25,248 --> 01:07:27,669
Them new fangled machines
down in Ticopi that's doing it.

1128
01:07:27,743 --> 01:07:29,085
Every day you traipse
down there with Buddie

1129
01:07:29,152 --> 01:07:30,461
and you come back
being different.

1130
01:07:30,527 --> 01:07:32,087
Half the time
you're feeling glad.

1131
01:07:32,159 --> 01:07:34,396
Like last week, they
tore up one of our fields.

1132
01:07:34,463 --> 01:07:36,983
Them machines don't care who's
been plowing there for 50 years.

1133
01:07:37,055 --> 01:07:38,943
The Tollivers don't
mean nothing to them.

1134
01:07:39,008 --> 01:07:40,699
I ain't nobody
with a high temper.

1135
01:07:40,768 --> 01:07:42,426
But you're talking
unreasonable.

1136
01:07:42,496 --> 01:07:43,870
We're getting rich,
ain't we?

1137
01:07:43,935 --> 01:07:46,139
Look at them five checks
over there in that bowI.

1138
01:07:46,207 --> 01:07:47,320
Half of them is yours.

1139
01:07:47,392 --> 01:07:50,141
And how did we get them?
Just doing nothing.

1140
01:07:50,208 --> 01:07:53,207
And if that's what you call
civilization, then I'm for it.

1141
01:07:53,279 --> 01:07:55,483
Judd!
He needs a-talking to.

1142
01:07:55,551 --> 01:07:57,526
It ain't right for no young
man to brood about nothing.

1143
01:07:57,600 --> 01:07:59,388
This you call
nothing, huh?

1144
01:07:59,456 --> 01:08:00,917
Listen, there's got to
be a change, you see?

1145
01:08:00,991 --> 01:08:02,201
Not for me,
there ain't.

1146
01:08:02,271 --> 01:08:03,351
There ain't no more
chance of me changing

1147
01:08:03,423 --> 01:08:05,594
than there is of that old Lonesome
Pine changed into a hickory.

1148
01:08:05,663 --> 01:08:07,671
I belong to the earth.
The plowed up soiI.

1149
01:08:07,744 --> 01:08:09,532
I was raised and
I'm gonna die in it.

1150
01:08:09,599 --> 01:08:11,006
You got what you like?
You can have it.

1151
01:08:11,071 --> 01:08:14,071
Me, I'm going back. Back
where my pappy raised me.

1152
01:08:16,479 --> 01:08:18,268
David, you can't
do that.

1153
01:08:18,335 --> 01:08:21,117
You're our boy.
I mean, you're like our boy.

1154
01:08:21,184 --> 01:08:23,093
I ain't a-wanting
you to go.

1155
01:08:27,200 --> 01:08:30,014
Two pink-eyed doves
sitting in a tree,

1156
01:08:30,432 --> 01:08:32,766
one for you, one for me.

1157
01:08:32,831 --> 01:08:34,108
For June.

1158
01:08:59,679 --> 01:09:04,982
<i>For when
it's twilight on the trail</i>

1159
01:09:05,952 --> 01:09:09,334
<i>And I jog along</i>

1160
01:09:09,856 --> 01:09:13,980
<i>The world is like a dream</i>

1161
01:09:14,271 --> 01:09:17,435
<i>And the ripple
of the stream</i>

1162
01:09:18,784 --> 01:09:21,598
<i>Is my song</i>

1163
01:09:22,528 --> 01:09:27,710
<i>For when it's twilight
on the trail</i>

1164
01:09:44,031 --> 01:09:45,624
Hello?

1165
01:09:46,367 --> 01:09:49,564
Well, well, well,
Miss Tolliver.

1166
01:09:50,016 --> 01:09:51,063
What, again?

1167
01:09:51,136 --> 01:09:52,118
Obviously.

1168
01:09:52,192 --> 01:09:54,199
Do I tell her
you're out to tea?

1169
01:09:54,271 --> 01:09:56,126
No, I'll talk to her.

1170
01:09:59,360 --> 01:10:01,978
You'd better go out and check
with Marks about those uprights.

1171
01:10:02,048 --> 01:10:03,324
Naturally.

1172
01:10:04,639 --> 01:10:05,817
Hello, June.

1173
01:10:05,888 --> 01:10:08,222
Are you mad at somebody
or something?

1174
01:10:08,287 --> 01:10:10,109
Well, you talk like it.

1175
01:10:11,488 --> 01:10:12,698
Oh, yeah.

1176
01:10:13,887 --> 01:10:16,026
Busy? You don't know
what busy means.

1177
01:10:16,096 --> 01:10:17,306
I ain't...

1178
01:10:17,375 --> 01:10:19,993
I mean, I haven't
had a minute to myself.

1179
01:10:20,543 --> 01:10:23,063
This morning I learnt
all about the Revolution.

1180
01:10:23,135 --> 01:10:25,023
It was just like a feud.

1181
01:10:25,631 --> 01:10:27,060
In 1775...

1182
01:10:28,447 --> 01:10:30,520
Wait a minute, June.
Come in.

1183
01:10:30,623 --> 01:10:32,347
Mr. Hale, we've got that slue banked.

1184
01:10:32,416 --> 01:10:33,626
That's fine, Taylor.

1185
01:10:33,695 --> 01:10:35,768
Wait a minute, get the steam
shoveI out on the bridge

1186
01:10:35,840 --> 01:10:37,301
so we can start to
fill in the morning.

1187
01:10:37,375 --> 01:10:38,749
Yes, sir.

1188
01:10:38,815 --> 01:10:40,222
Yeah, June?

1189
01:10:41,152 --> 01:10:42,199
Yeah.

1190
01:10:42,687 --> 01:10:45,982
But that wasn't Patrick Henry,
that was Lord Cornwallis.

1191
01:10:46,175 --> 01:10:47,288
Cornwallis.

1192
01:10:47,423 --> 01:10:48,852
All right. Cornwallis.

1193
01:10:48,928 --> 01:10:51,164
What difference
does it make?

1194
01:10:52,576 --> 01:10:53,852
How are you?

1195
01:10:55,583 --> 01:10:57,820
How's Pappy and Mammy
and Buddie?

1196
01:10:58,784 --> 01:10:59,798
They are?

1197
01:10:59,871 --> 01:11:00,918
Yeah.

1198
01:11:08,159 --> 01:11:11,225
Say, June, you know you've
got the prettiest eyes.

1199
01:11:12,031 --> 01:11:12,979
Yeah.

1200
01:11:14,303 --> 01:11:15,994
And the cutest nose.

1201
01:11:18,848 --> 01:11:20,735
Say, have you
got a dimple?

1202
01:11:30,079 --> 01:11:31,421
You get a fix, Son?

1203
01:11:31,487 --> 01:11:33,462
She's all sort onto the
bridge and ready to go.

1204
01:11:33,535 --> 01:11:35,096
We'll pop her off
in the morning.

1205
01:11:35,168 --> 01:11:37,655
Kind of like to have
Mr. Hale see it.

1206
01:12:00,799 --> 01:12:02,141
Hey, Pappy.

1207
01:12:02,303 --> 01:12:04,692
Now we're here
for Mr. Corsey?

1208
01:12:06,655 --> 01:12:08,510
Yeah, but you stay right
here till your pappy

1209
01:12:08,575 --> 01:12:10,363
gets through talking
to Mr. Hale.

1210
01:12:10,432 --> 01:12:11,806
Thanks, Pappy.

1211
01:12:28,735 --> 01:12:30,557
Can I come in,
Mr. Hale?

1212
01:12:31,007 --> 01:12:32,600
Sure, come on in.

1213
01:12:35,071 --> 01:12:37,886
I got serious things to
talk to you about, Mr. Hale.

1214
01:12:37,951 --> 01:12:38,900
Sit down.

1215
01:12:47,743 --> 01:12:49,499
And now, it's Dave
that's going away.

1216
01:12:49,567 --> 01:12:50,941
It's gotten me worried.

1217
01:12:51,008 --> 01:12:52,601
About Melissa, I mean.

1218
01:12:52,672 --> 01:12:54,711
She don't sing
no more, Mr. Hale.

1219
01:12:54,783 --> 01:12:57,434
Sun up always seen
her singing, you know?

1220
01:12:57,503 --> 01:12:59,892
I'm sorry about Melissa,
but there's nothing I can do.

1221
01:12:59,967 --> 01:13:01,396
I got troubles of my own.

1222
01:13:01,471 --> 01:13:03,293
You gotta come, Mr. Hale.

1223
01:13:03,359 --> 01:13:05,693
Melissa,
she'll listen to you.

1224
01:13:05,760 --> 01:13:07,865
Somehow, I don't talk
the right language to her.

1225
01:13:07,936 --> 01:13:10,172
No wonder you can't speak a
language which Melissa understands.

