01:23:12,894 --> 01:23:16,855
<i>Underneath the Lonesome Pine</i>

1383
01:23:19,807 --> 01:23:22,490
<i>On the hill</i>

1384
01:23:30,815 --> 01:23:35,070
Oh, God, our Heavenly Father, we
bow before thee in meekest humbleness

1385
01:23:35,775 --> 01:23:40,631
leaving in thy divine wisdom and
accepting with equaI humbleness

1386
01:23:41,086 --> 01:23:43,225
the complexities
of this life.

1387
01:23:44,126 --> 01:23:48,436
We are returning to the earth
that which thou has produced.

1388
01:23:49,086 --> 01:23:52,534
A part of thy souI,
of life eternaI.

1389
01:24:37,503 --> 01:24:40,372
There's just about
eight of them, Judd.

1390
01:24:40,639 --> 01:24:41,948
Dominickers!

1391
01:24:42,078 --> 01:24:44,729
Looks like things is just
born to the Tollivers.

1392
01:24:44,798 --> 01:24:46,391
Don't it, Melissa?

1393
01:24:46,911 --> 01:24:48,438
Sure seems.

1394
01:24:49,631 --> 01:24:50,940
What are we
going to do?

1395
01:24:51,007 --> 01:24:52,381
What are we
standing here for?

1396
01:24:52,446 --> 01:24:53,788
June, honey.

1397
01:24:53,854 --> 01:24:56,026
I'm not just gonna
stand around any longer.

1398
01:24:56,095 --> 01:24:57,436
Be sensible.

1399
01:25:05,759 --> 01:25:07,482
Before green-up
time, Dave.

1400
01:25:07,550 --> 01:25:09,306
That's what you want,
isn't it?

1401
01:25:13,791 --> 01:25:14,903
You mean it?

1402
01:25:14,974 --> 01:25:18,171
It's gotta be somebody
who acts like a Tolliver.

1403
01:25:18,239 --> 01:25:20,410
Is that what
it's going to be?

1404
01:25:31,550 --> 01:25:33,339
Dave, I don't
want you to go.

1405
01:25:33,406 --> 01:25:36,024
I ain't hating the Falins.
I ain't hating nobody.

1406
01:25:36,094 --> 01:25:37,687
I ain't grieving
for Buddie.

1407
01:25:37,758 --> 01:25:39,646
June's my sorrow now.

1408
01:25:39,711 --> 01:25:41,718
I don't want to
go on hating.

1409
01:25:42,046 --> 01:25:43,606
Don't go, David.

1410
01:25:45,182 --> 01:25:46,905
Dave...
Wait a minute.

1411
01:25:47,839 --> 01:25:49,627
Dave, you're not going to
let him... Dave, listen.

1412
01:25:49,694 --> 01:25:52,760
You can't do this thing. You've
got green-up time to think about.

1413
01:25:52,830 --> 01:25:54,619
You'll be
getting married, then.

1414
01:25:54,686 --> 01:25:56,923
Now you're going out and
run the risk of being killed.

1415
01:25:56,991 --> 01:25:58,518
Hasn't there been enough
unhappiness in this house?

1416
01:25:58,590 --> 01:25:59,572
You ain't a Tolliver.

1417
01:25:59,646 --> 01:26:00,595
You're an outsider.

1418
01:26:00,671 --> 01:26:02,100
Yes. Well, none of you could have

1419
01:26:02,174 --> 01:26:04,029
loved little Buddie
any better than I did.

1420
01:26:04,094 --> 01:26:06,877
And he was killed because I taught
him to love the things I did.

1421
01:26:06,943 --> 01:26:08,437
It was my fault.

1422
01:26:08,511 --> 01:26:11,194
And this matter of getting
even is gonna be my business.

1423
01:26:11,262 --> 01:26:13,335
It's gonna be my business untiI
I've cleaned out every Falin

1424
01:26:13,407 --> 01:26:15,643
that had anything
to do with it.

1425
01:26:19,454 --> 01:26:21,243
Jack! Jack!

1426
01:26:34,271 --> 01:26:35,383
Dave.

1427
01:26:36,030 --> 01:26:37,459
I didn't want him to go.

1428
01:26:37,534 --> 01:26:39,356
I wouldn't have
let you go, either.

1429
01:26:39,839 --> 01:26:41,781
I would have
stopped you.

1430
01:26:43,423 --> 01:26:46,554
I only said those things
'cause I was hurt inside.

1431
01:26:48,094 --> 01:26:49,785
I could've stopped you.

1432
01:26:49,854 --> 01:26:51,512
But he's different.

1433
01:26:51,582 --> 01:26:53,437
He's not like a brother.

1434
01:26:54,687 --> 01:26:56,443
He'll never come back.

1435
01:26:57,438 --> 01:26:59,609
He'll never
wanna come back.

1436
01:27:01,598 --> 01:27:02,711
Dave.

1437
01:27:03,966 --> 01:27:05,428
Stop him.

1438
01:27:05,503 --> 01:27:07,291
Tell him what I can't.

1439
01:27:09,247 --> 01:27:10,654
Please, Dave.

1440
01:27:31,582 --> 01:27:32,826
You ain't going
to no Falins.

1441
01:27:32,895 --> 01:27:35,000
No? Well,
you try and stop me.

1442
01:27:35,070 --> 01:27:38,518
You're looking for trouble, Mr.
Hale, the mountains is full of it.

1443
01:28:10,079 --> 01:28:11,737
We're all brave men.

1444
01:28:12,095 --> 01:28:14,200
Falins are brave men.

1445
01:28:14,623 --> 01:28:15,702
You killed
the children.

1446
01:28:15,774 --> 01:28:17,433
I didn't know.

1447
01:28:17,503 --> 01:28:18,932
It's done now.

1448
01:28:19,454 --> 01:28:21,821
Sometime,
I'll wanna go downtown.

1449
01:28:22,238 --> 01:28:24,180
People, they'll look at me.

1450
01:28:24,831 --> 01:28:28,442
Maybe when I ain't around,
they'll call me Herod.

1451
01:28:29,598 --> 01:28:31,060
Herod Falin.

1452
01:28:31,998 --> 01:28:33,940
They might call me that.

1453
01:28:34,366 --> 01:28:36,374
He was a fellow
that done that once.

1454
01:28:36,446 --> 01:28:37,690
He killed babies.

1455
01:28:37,758 --> 01:28:39,482
The kid was a Tolliver,
wasn't he?

1456
01:28:39,550 --> 01:28:41,273
You're kind of forgetting
about Jim, ain't you?

1457
01:28:41,342 --> 01:28:42,935
I ain't
forgetting nothing.

1458
01:28:43,006 --> 01:28:45,908
Jim told me, in my arms, he
was hiding behind the bushes

1459
01:28:45,982 --> 01:28:47,706
